shared_text:
African American Parent Support Group: Parent-Student Organization
July 14 at 8:17 AM ·

Join us on Wednesday July 15th as we kickoff our Student Social Activism Summer series with our Netflix Party viewing of the documentary the 13th. Filmmaker Ava DuVernay explores the history of racial inequality in the United States, focusing on the fact that the nation's prisons are disproportionately filled with African-Americans.

To view, you will need to download the Netflix Party App on your laptop. Go to https://www.netflixparty.com/ for download instructions.

Click here to register: https://tinyurl.com/y9jnyyha for the 6pm or 6:30pm viewing.

This is part of a Harvard SPARKS public service project coordinated by WWP Student Alumni Jillian Medina.

Although adults are welcome, this program is designed by students for students.

PRESS RELEASE
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE:
For more information, contact: AAPSG Communications @ wwpaapsg@gmail.com

As of July 1, 2020 Latoya Edwards is the new President for the 2020-2021 school year. Latoya takes over from President Joy Horton who recently moved out of the WWP school district. Gregg White continues in his officer role as VP of Outreach and Grace Odediran will continue as our Treasurer.

Joy Horton will assist with the transition and help the organization in an non officer role with communications and other programs.

Please read the full press release on our website at https://wwpaapsg.weebly.com/.

post_text:
Dear WW-P Parents/Guardians,

The WW-P Genesis Parent Portal will close July 9, 2020, and reopen July 20, 2020. During this time, parents/guardians will not have access to the system as it updates for the 2020-2021 school year.

Upon the system reopening July 20, parents are asked to check and confirm that personal contact (email/phone number) and emergency contact information is up-to-date in the system. Student scheduling and placement information will not be available at this time. The information will be forthcoming later in the summer.

On Aug. 4, 2020, district required forms for students will be available via the Parent Portal for completion by parent/guardian #1 for each district student. At that time, parents will be able to login to the Genesis Parent Portal and read, review, and complete all mandatory district forms. Please note that there are forms for each student, and there are different forms for different grade levels.

If you need assistance with your Genesis account, please send an email to wwpsis@ww-p.org.

shared_text:
Plainsboro Township Police Department
March 11 at 11:43 AM ·

On Tuesday, March 10th, Chief Fred Tavener presented Officer Jesus "Jay" Martinez with the Plainsboro Township Life Saving Award for his prompt and alert observations on February 12, 2020 at Millstone River School.

Officer Martinez observed a distressed male with skin discoloration and dilated pupils. He immediately identified these signs as a medical emergency and alerted the school administrators and nurse. It was later determined that the male was having cardiac complications which required emergency surgery.

Officer Martinez’s quick response, recognition of the medical emergency and immediate actions resulted directly in the saving of the man’s life.

post_text:
WW-P parents and staff are invited to attend several upcoming presentations and workshops regarding student wellness in the local area. All events are free community events.

Nov. 13 — The Big Disconnect: Family Life in the Digital Era. Hamilton Township School District is sponsoring a presentation by Dr. Catherine Steiner-Adair titled, “The Big Disconnect: Family Life in the Digital Era” Nov. 13, 7 p.m. at Reynolds Middle School (2145 Yardville-Hamilton Square Rd.) in Hamilton Township. Attendees are required to pre-register online → bit.ly/36WRxVV

Nov. 21 — Parenting in the Age of Social Media. The second workshop in the WW-P Parent University series. This presentation will be held Nov. 21, 7 p.m. at Grover Middle School → bit.ly/2I52PwP

Nov. 25 — Teen Vaping: What You Need to Know. Sponsored by Governor’s Council on Alcoholism and Drug Abuse, the evening will include a presentation by Dr. Michael Steinberg, director of Rutgers Tobacco Dependence Program Nov. 25, 7 p.m. at Princeton High School Performing Arts Center → bit.ly/2X4eEJD
